[8/8] Creating image`, entirely inside Native Image object-file writing:\n\n```text\njava.lang.InternalError: a fault occurred in an unsafe memory access operation\n  at java.base/jdk.internal.misc.ScopedMemoryAccess.copyMemoryInternal\n  ...\n  at com.oracle.objectfile.ObjectFile.writeBuffer\n  at com.oracle.objectfile.ObjectFile.write\n  at com.oracle.svm.hosted.image.NativeImage.write\n```\n\nThere is no stack frame from:\n\n- `gnu.trove.*`\n- `net_sf_trove4j.core.*`\n- JUnit test execution\n- metadata loading\n- reflection/resource/proxy/serialization config handling\n\nSo I would not change the test to mask this. The added test is still the right targeted coverage for:\n\n```text\ngnu.trove.map.hash.THashMap$MapBackedView.toArray(T[])\n -> java.lang.reflect.Array.newInstance(...)\n```\n\nRecommended next steps for this specific failure are environment/toolchain oriented:\n\n```bash\n./gradlew clean -Pcoordinates=net.sf.trove4j:core:3.1.0\n./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=net.sf.trove4j:core:3.1.0 --no-daemon --stacktrace\n```\n\nIf it reproduces, this should be treated as a Native Image builder bug in the GraalVM `25.1.0-dev+10.1` toolchain, not as a test defect. The relevant error report is already generated at:\n\n```text\ntests/src/net.sf.trove4j/core/3.1.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/svm_err_b_20260506T150123.604_pid3326938.md\n```", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a4304b3dcc141f30169fb3bf4c0ec81958472bfdb34e55788\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5850, "output": 1339, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38421, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778072544629, "responseId": "resp_0a4304b3dcc141f30169fb3be116c081958b3b7c96b8e876d3"}}
